<br>
Great site, but I noticed that the point allocation is different for Barbarian Rogues on www.castersrealm.com that suggests to<br>
Add 20 to Stamina, 5 to Strength, 5 to Dexterity. <br>
<br>
RACE STR STA AGI DEX WIS INT CHA <br>
Barbarian 108 115 92 85 70 60 55 <br>
<br>
*perhaps the above is outdated information (?!)*<br>
<br>
This site suggests to <br>
Add 25 to Strength, 5 to Dexterity. <br>
<br>
RACE STR STA AGI DEX WIS INT CHA <br>
Barbarian 128 95 92 85 70 60 55 <br>
<br>
Can you please clarify this for me, that is, what is the best allocation of points, and what the benefits would be? I like the original idea of increasing stamina, thereby increasing HP, having read on other posts increasing strength is easily recovered by equiping STR items.  <br>
<br>
I welcome other comments and opinions relating to this. <br>
<br>
J. Iscariot<br>
Bar Rogue<br>
Drinal<br>
